In this article, President Obama discusses the progress and challenges facing the VA (Veterans Affairs) system. He acknowledges the significant problems that have occurred, such as long wait times and inadequate service for veterans, but also highlights the improvements that have been made. The President emphasizes the need to continue addressing issues, particularly in implementing the Choice Act, which allows veterans to seek private sector care if they have difficulty accessing a VA facility. Mental health and suicide prevention are also mentioned as areas that require more attention. Additionally, President Obama stresses the importance of restoring trust and confidence in the VA system and ensuring a culture of customer service. Despite the problems, he recognizes the outstanding care provided by many doctors, nurses, and staff within the VA. The President thanks everyone for their input and expresses gratitude to the members of Congress who have been actively involved in addressing these issues.